cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on the lambda calculus and its axiomatization for lazy evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses consistency and standardization properties, which are related to logic and proof theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely sub-category. The paper also establishes a correspondence with Launchbury's natural semantics, which falls under cs.TL (Computational Theory). The paper also discusses the problems with existing calculi and proposes an alternative, which involves the use of contexts, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the lambda calculus and its properties also makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
